No, TripleDES (3DES) is **NOT safe** for new applications and has been deprecated by NIST since 2017. Both DES and 3DES use 64-bit block sizes, making them vulnerable to the Sweet32 birthday attack (CVE-2016-2183). In 2023, several healthcare organizations faced breaches due to legacy 3DES encryption.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```csharp
