**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Credentials transmitted in plaintext can be captured by anyone on the network
- Session tokens can be stolen enabling complete account takeover
- All PII and sensitive data is visible to network observers
- MITM attackers can modify requests and responses in transit
- Violates PCI-DSS, HIPAA, GDPR requirements for data in transit

**SECURE VERSION**:

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const https = require('https');
const fs = require('fs');
const helmet = require('helmet');
const bodyParser = require('body-parser');

const app = express();

// Security headers including HSTS
app.use(helmet({
  hsts: {
    maxAge: 31536000, // 1 year
    includeSubDomains: true,
    preload: true
  },
  contentSecurityPolicy: true
}));

app.use(bodyParser.json());

// TLS configuration with strong cipher suites
const tlsOptions = {
  key: fs.readFileSync('./certs/server.key'),
  cert: fs.readFileSync('./certs/server.crt'),
  ca: fs.readFileSync('./certs/ca.crt'),

  // Enforce TLS 1.2 minimum
  minVersion: 'TLSv1.2',

  // Strong cipher suites only
  ciphers: [
    'ECDHE-ECDSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256',
    'ECDHE-RSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256',
    'ECDHE-ECDSA-AES256-GCM-SHA384',
    'ECDHE-RSA-AES256-GCM-SHA384'
  ].join(':'),

  // Prefer server cipher order
  honorCipherOrder: true
};

// Create HTTPS server
const server = https.createServer(tlsOptions, app);

// Redirect HTTP to HTTPS
const http = require('http');
http.createServer((req, res) => {
  res.writeHead(301, { Location: `https://${req.headers.host}${req.url}` });
  res.end();
}).listen(80);

// Secure login endpoint
app.post('/api/login', (req, res) => {
  const { username, password } = req.body;

  authenticateUser(username, password)
    .then(user => {
      const sessionToken = generateSessionToken(user.id);
      // Secure cookie settings
      res.cookie('session', sessionToken, {
        httpOnly: true,
        secure: true, // Only over HTTPS
        sameSite: 'strict',
        maxAge: 3600000
      });
      res.json({ user: { id: user.id, name: user.name } });
    })
    .catch(err => res.status(401).json({ error: 'Invalid credentials' }));
});

server.listen(443, () => {
  console.log('Secure server running on https://localhost:443');
});
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **TLS encryption**: All data encrypted in transit using strong cipher suites
- **HSTS header**: Browsers remember to always use HTTPS, preventing downgrade attacks
- **HTTP redirect**: Forces all connections to upgrade to HTTPS
- **Secure cookies**: httpOnly, secure, and sameSite flags prevent token theft
- **Modern TLS versions**: TLS 1.2+ prevents known protocol vulnerabilities

Yes, internal services absolutely need TLS! The 2023 Drizly breach and countless others occurred because attackers who gained initial access moved laterally through unencrypted internal networks. Zero Trust architecture requires encryption everywhere.

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const https = require('https');
const axios = require('axios');
