GraphQL authorization is complex because the flexible query structure allows attackers to bypass security checks. Unlike REST APIs where endpoints map clearly to permissions, GraphQL lets clients request any combination of fields and nested objects.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```java
import graphql.schema.DataFetcher;
import graphql.schema.DataFetchingEnvironment;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.Map;

@Component
public class UserDataFetcher implements DataFetcher<User> {

    private final UserRepository userRepository;
    private final OrderRepository orderRepository;

    public UserDataFetcher(UserRepository userRepository, OrderRepository orderRepository) {
        this.userRepository = userRepository;
        this.orderRepository = orderRepository;
    }

    @Override
    public User get(DataFetchingEnvironment environment) {
        // VULNERABLE: Only checks if user is authenticated, not authorized
        String requestedUserId = environment.getArgument("id");

        // No verification that authenticated user can access this specific user's data
        return userRepository.findById(requestedUserId);
    }
}

@Component
public class OrderDataFetcher implements DataFetcher<List<Order>> {

    private final OrderRepository orderRepository;

    @Override
    public List<Order> get(DataFetchingEnvironment environment) {
        // VULNERABLE: Gets parent user without authorization check
        User parentUser = environment.getSource();

        // Returns all orders for any user the client requests
        return orderRepository.findByUserId(parentUser.getId());
    }
}
```

**Attack Payload**:
```graphql
# Attacker authenticated as user "attacker123" queries victim's data
query StealUserData {
  user(id: "victim456") {
    id
    email
    ssn
    creditCards {
      number
      expiry
      cvv
    }
    orders {
      id
      items
      shippingAddress
    }
  }
  # Alias attack to query multiple users in one request
  admin: user(id: "admin001") {
    email
    role
    permissions
  }
}
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- No field-level authorization: Any authenticated user can query any other user's data
- Nested resolver bypass: Child resolvers trust parent context without re-validating authorization
- Alias attacks allow batch extraction of multiple users' data in single request
- Introspection exposes schema, helping attackers discover sensitive fields

**SECURE VERSION**:

```java
import graphql.schema.DataFetcher;
import graphql.schema.DataFetchingEnvironment;
import org.springframework.security.core.context.SecurityContextHolder;
import org.springframework.security.access.AccessDeniedException;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;
import org.slf4j.Logger;
import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;
import java.util.List;

@Component
public class SecureUserDataFetcher implements DataFetcher<User> {

    private static final Logger auditLog = LoggerFactory.getLogger("AUDIT");
    private final UserRepository userRepository;
    private final AuthorizationService authService;

    public SecureUserDataFetcher(UserRepository userRepository, AuthorizationService authService) {
        this.userRepository = userRepository;
        this.authService = authService;
    }

    @Override
    public User get(DataFetchingEnvironment environment) {
        // Get authenticated user from security context
        AuthenticatedUser currentUser = (AuthenticatedUser) SecurityContextHolder
            .getContext().getAuthentication().getPrincipal();

        String requestedUserId = environment.getArgument("id");

        // SECURE: Verify authorization for specific resource
        if (!authService.canAccessUser(currentUser, requestedUserId)) {
            auditLog.warn("ACCESS_DENIED: User {} attempted to access user {} data",
                currentUser.getId(), requestedUserId);
            throw new AccessDeniedException("Not authorized to access this user's data");
        }

        User user = userRepository.findById(requestedUserId);

        // SECURE: Apply field-level filtering based on permissions
        return authService.filterSensitiveFields(user, currentUser);
    }
}

@Component
public class AuthorizationService {

    public boolean canAccessUser(AuthenticatedUser requester, String targetUserId) {
        // Users can access their own data
        if (requester.getId().equals(targetUserId)) {
            return true;
        }
        // Admins can access any user
        if (requester.hasRole("ADMIN")) {
            return true;
        }
        // Support staff can access users they are assigned to
        if (requester.hasRole("SUPPORT") && 
            requester.getAssignedUserIds().contains(targetUserId)) {
            return true;
        }
        return false;
    }

    public User filterSensitiveFields(User user, AuthenticatedUser requester) {
        // Non-admins cannot see SSN, internal notes, etc.
        if (!requester.hasRole("ADMIN")) {
            user.setSsn(null);
            user.setInternalNotes(null);
        }
        return user;
    }
}
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **Resource-level authorization**: Each query explicitly checks if the requester can access the specific resource being requested
- **Security context propagation**: Authentication info flows through GraphQL context for consistent authorization
- **Field-level filtering**: Sensitive fields are masked based on requester's role and permissions
- **Audit logging**: All access attempts, especially denials, are logged for security monitoring

Nested authorization is where most GraphQL vulnerabilities occur. Each resolver must independently verify authorization - you cannot trust that parent resolvers performed adequate checks. Here's a production-ready pattern with depth limiting and comprehensive authorization.

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```java
import graphql.ExecutionResult;
import graphql.GraphQL;
import graphql.analysis.MaxQueryComplexityInstrumentation;
import graphql.analysis.MaxQueryDepthInstrumentation;
import graphql.execution.instrumentation.ChainedInstrumentation;
import graphql.schema.DataFetcher;
import graphql.schema.DataFetchingEnvironment;
import graphql.schema.GraphQLFieldDefinition;
import graphql.schema.idl.RuntimeWiring;
import org.springframework.context.annotation.Bean;
import org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;
import org.springframework.security.access.AccessDeniedException;
import org.slf4j.Logger;
import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;
import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture;

@Configuration
public class SecureGraphQLConfiguration {

    private static final Logger auditLog = LoggerFactory.getLogger("AUDIT");
    private static final int MAX_QUERY_DEPTH = 5;
    private static final int MAX_QUERY_COMPLEXITY = 100;

    @Bean
    public GraphQL graphQL(GraphQLSchema schema) {
        // DEFENSE IN DEPTH: Limit query depth and complexity
        return GraphQL.newGraphQL(schema)
            .instrumentation(new ChainedInstrumentation(Arrays.asList(
                new MaxQueryDepthInstrumentation(MAX_QUERY_DEPTH),
                new MaxQueryComplexityInstrumentation(MAX_QUERY_COMPLEXITY),
                new AuthorizationInstrumentation()
            )))
            .build();
    }
}

// Custom instrumentation for authorization tracking
public class AuthorizationInstrumentation extends SimpleInstrumentation {

    @Override
    public InstrumentationContext<ExecutionResult> beginExecution(
            InstrumentationExecutionParameters parameters) {
        // Store authorization context for nested resolvers
        AuthorizationContext authCtx = new AuthorizationContext();
        parameters.getGraphQLContext().put(AuthorizationContext.class, authCtx);
        return super.beginExecution(parameters);
    }
}

// Context holder for authorization state across nested resolvers
public class AuthorizationContext {
    private final Set<String> authorizedResources = new ConcurrentHashSet<>();
    private final Map<String, Set<String>> allowedFields = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();

    public void recordAuthorization(String resourceType, String resourceId) {
        authorizedResources.add(resourceType + ":" + resourceId);
    }

    public boolean isAuthorized(String resourceType, String resourceId) {
        return authorizedResources.contains(resourceType + ":" + resourceId);
    }
}

// Base class for secure data fetchers with built-in authorization
public abstract class SecureDataFetcher<T> implements DataFetcher<T> {

    protected static final Logger auditLog = LoggerFactory.getLogger("AUDIT");
    protected final AuthorizationService authService;

    protected SecureDataFetcher(AuthorizationService authService) {
        this.authService = authService;
    }

    @Override
    public final T get(DataFetchingEnvironment env) throws Exception {
        AuthenticatedUser currentUser = getCurrentUser(env);
        AuthorizationContext authCtx = env.getGraphQlContext().get(AuthorizationContext.class);

        // Template method: subclasses implement authorization logic
        if (!isAuthorized(env, currentUser, authCtx)) {
            String resourceInfo = getResourceIdentifier(env);
            auditLog.warn("GRAPHQL_AUTH_DENIED: user={}, resource={}, path={}",
                currentUser.getId(), resourceInfo, env.getExecutionStepInfo().getPath());
            throw new AccessDeniedException("Not authorized to access " + resourceInfo);
        }

        T result = fetchData(env, currentUser);

        // Record successful authorization for nested queries
        recordAuthorizationForNested(env, authCtx, result);

        return result;
    }

    protected abstract boolean isAuthorized(DataFetchingEnvironment env, 
        AuthenticatedUser user, AuthorizationContext authCtx);
    protected abstract T fetchData(DataFetchingEnvironment env, AuthenticatedUser user);
    protected abstract String getResourceIdentifier(DataFetchingEnvironment env);
    protected abstract void recordAuthorizationForNested(DataFetchingEnvironment env,
        AuthorizationContext authCtx, T result);

    protected AuthenticatedUser getCurrentUser(DataFetchingEnvironment env) {
        return env.getGraphQlContext().get(AuthenticatedUser.class);
    }
}

// Secure user fetcher with nested authorization support
@Component
public class SecureUserFetcher extends SecureDataFetcher<User> {

    private final UserRepository userRepository;

    public SecureUserFetcher(AuthorizationService authService, UserRepository userRepository) {
        super(authService);
        this.userRepository = userRepository;
    }

    @Override
    protected boolean isAuthorized(DataFetchingEnvironment env, 
            AuthenticatedUser user, AuthorizationContext authCtx) {
        String requestedUserId = env.getArgument("id");
        return authService.canAccessUser(user, requestedUserId);
    }

    @Override
    protected User fetchData(DataFetchingEnvironment env, AuthenticatedUser user) {
        String requestedUserId = env.getArgument("id");
        User targetUser = userRepository.findById(requestedUserId);

        // Apply field-level filtering
        return authService.filterUserFields(targetUser, user, getRequestedFields(env));
    }

    @Override
    protected String getResourceIdentifier(DataFetchingEnvironment env) {
        return "User:" + env.getArgument("id");
    }

    @Override
    protected void recordAuthorizationForNested(DataFetchingEnvironment env,
            AuthorizationContext authCtx, User result) {
        // Record that this user's nested resources can be accessed
        authCtx.recordAuthorization("User", result.getId());
        authCtx.recordAuthorization("UserOrders", result.getId());
    }

    private Set<String> getRequestedFields(DataFetchingEnvironment env) {
        return env.getSelectionSet().getFields().stream()
            .map(f -> f.getName())
            .collect(Collectors.toSet());
    }
}

// Nested order fetcher - MUST re-verify authorization
@Component
public class SecureOrderFetcher extends SecureDataFetcher<List<Order>> {

    private final OrderRepository orderRepository;

    public SecureOrderFetcher(AuthorizationService authService, OrderRepository orderRepository) {
        super(authService);
        this.orderRepository = orderRepository;
    }

    @Override
    protected boolean isAuthorized(DataFetchingEnvironment env,
            AuthenticatedUser user, AuthorizationContext authCtx) {
        User parentUser = env.getSource();

        // CRITICAL: Re-verify authorization even for nested queries
        // Don't trust that parent resolver checked correctly
        if (!authCtx.isAuthorized("UserOrders", parentUser.getId())) {
            auditLog.error("NESTED_AUTH_BYPASS_ATTEMPT: user={}, targetUser={}",
                user.getId(), parentUser.getId());
            return false;
        }

        // Additional check: verify current user can still access
        return authService.canAccessUserOrders(user, parentUser.getId());
    }

    @Override
    protected List<Order> fetchData(DataFetchingEnvironment env, AuthenticatedUser user) {
        User parentUser = env.getSource();
        List<Order> orders = orderRepository.findByUserId(parentUser.getId());

        // Filter sensitive order fields based on permissions
        return orders.stream()
            .map(order -> authService.filterOrderFields(order, user))
            .collect(Collectors.toList());
    }

    @Override
    protected String getResourceIdentifier(DataFetchingEnvironment env) {
        User parentUser = env.getSource();
        return "Orders:user=" + parentUser.getId();
    }

    @Override
    protected void recordAuthorizationForNested(DataFetchingEnvironment env,
            AuthorizationContext authCtx, List<Order> result) {
        result.forEach(order -> authCtx.recordAuthorization("Order", order.getId()));
    }
}

// Production GraphQL controller with rate limiting and monitoring
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/graphql")
public class SecureGraphQLController {

    private static final Logger auditLog = LoggerFactory.getLogger("AUDIT");
    private final GraphQL graphQL;
    private final RateLimiter rateLimiter;
    private final MetricsService metrics;

    @PostMapping
    @RateLimited(requests = 100, per = Duration.ofMinutes(1))
    public ResponseEntity<Map<String, Object>> execute(
            @RequestBody GraphQLRequest request,
            @AuthenticationPrincipal AuthenticatedUser user,
            HttpServletRequest httpRequest) {

        long startTime = System.currentTimeMillis();

        // SECURITY: Disable introspection in production
        if (isIntrospectionQuery(request.getQuery()) && isProduction()) {
            auditLog.warn("INTROSPECTION_BLOCKED: user={}, ip={}",
                user.getId(), httpRequest.getRemoteAddr());
            return ResponseEntity.status(403)
                .body(Map.of("error", "Introspection disabled"));
        }

        // Build execution context with user info
        ExecutionInput executionInput = ExecutionInput.newExecutionInput()
            .query(request.getQuery())
            .variables(request.getVariables())
            .graphQLContext(builder -> builder
                .put(AuthenticatedUser.class, user)
                .put("clientIp", httpRequest.getRemoteAddr()))
            .build();

        try {
            ExecutionResult result = graphQL.execute(executionInput);

            // Log query execution for monitoring
            auditLog.info("GRAPHQL_QUERY: user={}, duration={}ms, errors={}",
                user.getId(), 
                System.currentTimeMillis() - startTime,
                result.getErrors().size());

            metrics.recordGraphQLQuery(user.getId(), 
                System.currentTimeMillis() - startTime,
                result.getErrors().isEmpty());

            return ResponseEntity.ok(result.toSpecification());

        } catch (AccessDeniedException e) {
            metrics.recordAuthorizationDenial(user.getId());
            return ResponseEntity.status(403)
                .body(Map.of("error", "Access denied"));
        }
    }

    private boolean isIntrospectionQuery(String query) {
        return query != null && 
            (query.contains("__schema") || query.contains("__type"));
    }

    private boolean isProduction() {
        return "production".equals(System.getenv("ENVIRONMENT"));
    }
}
