**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Reveals internal database schema (table names, column names like `password_hash`, `ssn`)
- Exposes file system paths (`/var/www/app/src/controllers/`)
- Shows SQL queries that can be analyzed for injection points
- Discloses technology stack versions through stack traces
- Helps attackers map internal network (`db.internal.company.com`)

**SECURE VERSION**:

