Storing encryption keys as constants in your code is one of the most dangerous cryptographic practices. Hard-coded keys can be extracted from compiled bytecode, version control history, or memory dumps, compromising all data encrypted with that key across every deployment.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```java
import javax.crypto.Cipher;
import javax.crypto.spec.SecretKeySpec;
import javax.crypto.spec.IvParameterSpec;
import java.util.Base64;
import java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;

public class DataEncryptor {
    // VULNERABLE: Hard-coded encryption key
    private static final String SECRET_KEY = "MySecretKey12345";
    private static final String INIT_VECTOR = "RandomInitVector";

    public static String encrypt(String plaintext) throws Exception {
        IvParameterSpec iv = new IvParameterSpec(INIT_VECTOR.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8));
        SecretKeySpec keySpec = new SecretKeySpec(SECRET_KEY.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8), "AES");

        Cipher cipher = Cipher.getInstance("AES/CBC/PKCS5PADDING");
        cipher.init(Cipher.ENCRYPT_MODE, keySpec, iv);

        byte[] encrypted = cipher.doFinal(plaintext.getBytes());
        return Base64.getEncoder().encodeToString(encrypted);
    }

    public static String decrypt(String ciphertext) throws Exception {
        IvParameterSpec iv = new IvParameterSpec(INIT_VECTOR.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8));
        SecretKeySpec keySpec = new SecretKeySpec(SECRET_KEY.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8), "AES");

        Cipher cipher = Cipher.getInstance("AES/CBC/PKCS5PADDING");
        cipher.init(Cipher.DECRYPT_MODE, keySpec, iv);

        byte[] decrypted = cipher.doFinal(Base64.getDecoder().decode(ciphertext));
        return new String(decrypted);
    }
}
```

**Attack Method**:
```bash
# Decompile the JAR to extract hard-coded key
jad -o -r -sjava -d output/ application.jar
grep -r "SECRET_KEY\|MySecretKey" output/

# Or use strings command on compiled class
strings DataEncryptor.class | grep -E '.{16}'

# Once key is extracted, decrypt any data from any deployment
java DecryptWithExtractedKey "MySecretKey12345" "encrypted_data_from_database"
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Key is visible in decompiled bytecode within seconds
- Same key used across all application instances - one compromise affects everyone
- Key appears in version control history, backup files, and memory dumps
- Impossible to rotate keys without application redeployment
- Static IV combined with static key enables pattern analysis attacks

**SECURE VERSION**:

```java
import javax.crypto.Cipher;
import javax.crypto.KeyGenerator;
import javax.crypto.SecretKey;
import javax.crypto.spec.GCMParameterSpec;
import javax.crypto.spec.SecretKeySpec;
import java.security.SecureRandom;
import java.util.Base64;

public class SecureDataEncryptor {
    private static final int GCM_IV_LENGTH = 12;
    private static final int GCM_TAG_LENGTH = 128;
    private static final String ALGORITHM = "AES/GCM/NoPadding";

    private final SecretKey secretKey;
    private final SecureRandom secureRandom;

    // Constructor loads key from secure external source
    public SecureDataEncryptor() throws Exception {
        this.secretKey = loadKeyFromSecureSource();
        this.secureRandom = new SecureRandom();
    }

    private SecretKey loadKeyFromSecureSource() throws Exception {
        // Option 1: Environment variable (base64 encoded)
        String keyBase64 = System.getenv("ENCRYPTION_KEY");
        if (keyBase64 == null || keyBase64.isEmpty()) {
            throw new SecurityException("Encryption key not configured");
        }
        byte[] keyBytes = Base64.getDecoder().decode(keyBase64);
        return new SecretKeySpec(keyBytes, "AES");
    }

    public String encrypt(String plaintext) throws Exception {
        // Generate random IV for each encryption
        byte[] iv = new byte[GCM_IV_LENGTH];
        secureRandom.nextBytes(iv);

        Cipher cipher = Cipher.getInstance(ALGORITHM);
        GCMParameterSpec parameterSpec = new GCMParameterSpec(GCM_TAG_LENGTH, iv);
        cipher.init(Cipher.ENCRYPT_MODE, secretKey, parameterSpec);

        byte[] encrypted = cipher.doFinal(plaintext.getBytes("UTF-8"));

        // Prepend IV to ciphertext for storage
        byte[] combined = new byte[iv.length + encrypted.length];
        System.arraycopy(iv, 0, combined, 0, iv.length);
        System.arraycopy(encrypted, 0, combined, iv.length, encrypted.length);

        return Base64.getEncoder().encodeToString(combined);
    }

    public String decrypt(String ciphertext) throws Exception {
        byte[] combined = Base64.getDecoder().decode(ciphertext);

        // Extract IV from the beginning
        byte[] iv = new byte[GCM_IV_LENGTH];
        System.arraycopy(combined, 0, iv, 0, iv.length);

        // Extract actual ciphertext
        byte[] encrypted = new byte[combined.length - iv.length];
        System.arraycopy(combined, iv.length, encrypted, 0, encrypted.length);

        Cipher cipher = Cipher.getInstance(ALGORITHM);
        GCMParameterSpec parameterSpec = new GCMParameterSpec(GCM_TAG_LENGTH, iv);
        cipher.init(Cipher.DECRYPT_MODE, secretKey, parameterSpec);

        return new String(cipher.doFinal(encrypted), "UTF-8");
    }
}
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **External Key Storage**: Key loaded from environment variable, never in code
- **AES-GCM Mode**: Provides both confidentiality and integrity (authenticated encryption)
- **Random IV Per Encryption**: Each encryption uses a unique IV, preventing pattern analysis
- **Fail-Secure Design**: Application fails to start if key not properly configured

Excellent concern. Production systems should use dedicated Key Management Services (KMS) or Hardware Security Modules (HSM) that provide secure key storage, automatic rotation, access controls, and audit logging. Here's a production-ready implementation.

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```java
import javax.crypto.Cipher;
import javax.crypto.SecretKey;
import javax.crypto.spec.GCMParameterSpec;
import javax.crypto.spec.SecretKeySpec;
import java.security.SecureRandom;
import java.util.Base64;
import java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentHashMap;
import java.util.logging.Logger;
import com.amazonaws.services.kms.AWSKMS;
import com.amazonaws.services.kms.AWSKMSClientBuilder;
import com.amazonaws.services.kms.model.*;

public class EnterpriseEncryptionService {
    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(EnterpriseEncryptionService.class.getName());
    private static final int GCM_IV_LENGTH = 12;
    private static final int GCM_TAG_LENGTH = 128;
    private static final String ALGORITHM = "AES/GCM/NoPadding";
    private static final int KEY_VERSION_BYTE_LENGTH = 4;

    private final AWSKMS kmsClient;
    private final String masterKeyId;
    private final SecureRandom secureRandom;
    private final ConcurrentHashMap<Integer, CachedKey> keyCache;
    private volatile int currentKeyVersion;

    private static class CachedKey {
        final SecretKey key;
        final long expirationTime;

        CachedKey(SecretKey key, long ttlMillis) {
            this.key = key;
            this.expirationTime = System.currentTimeMillis() + ttlMillis;
        }

        boolean isExpired() {
            return System.currentTimeMillis() > expirationTime;
        }
    }

    public EnterpriseEncryptionService(String kmsKeyArn) {
        this.kmsClient = AWSKMSClientBuilder.standard().build();
        this.masterKeyId = kmsKeyArn;
        this.secureRandom = new SecureRandom();
        this.keyCache = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();
        this.currentKeyVersion = 1;

        // Validate KMS connectivity on startup
        validateKmsAccess();
        logger.info("EnterpriseEncryptionService initialized with KMS key: " + maskKeyId(kmsKeyArn));
    }

    private void validateKmsAccess() {
        try {
            DescribeKeyRequest request = new DescribeKeyRequest().withKeyId(masterKeyId);
            DescribeKeyResult result = kmsClient.describeKey(request);
            if (!result.getKeyMetadata().isEnabled()) {
                throw new SecurityException("KMS key is disabled");
            }
        } catch (Exception e) {
            logger.severe("Failed to validate KMS access: " + e.getMessage());
            throw new SecurityException("KMS initialization failed", e);
        }
    }

    private SecretKey getDataEncryptionKey(int version) throws Exception {
        CachedKey cached = keyCache.get(version);
        if (cached != null && !cached.isExpired()) {
            return cached.key;
        }

        synchronized (this) {
            // Double-check after acquiring lock
            cached = keyCache.get(version);
            if (cached != null && !cached.isExpired()) {
                return cached.key;
            }

            // Generate new data key using KMS
            GenerateDataKeyRequest request = new GenerateDataKeyRequest()
                .withKeyId(masterKeyId)
                .withKeySpec(DataKeySpec.AES_256)
                .withEncryptionContext(java.util.Map.of(
                    "purpose", "data-encryption",
                    "version", String.valueOf(version)
                ));

            GenerateDataKeyResult result = kmsClient.generateDataKey(request);
            byte[] plaintextKey = result.getPlaintext().array();
            SecretKey dataKey = new SecretKeySpec(plaintextKey, "AES");

            // Clear plaintext from memory after creating key
            java.util.Arrays.fill(plaintextKey, (byte) 0);

            // Cache for 5 minutes
            keyCache.put(version, new CachedKey(dataKey, 300_000));
            logger.fine("Generated new data encryption key, version: " + version);

            return dataKey;
        }
    }

    public String encrypt(String plaintext, String context) throws Exception {
        if (plaintext == null || plaintext.isEmpty()) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Plaintext cannot be null or empty");
        }

        long startTime = System.currentTimeMillis();
        int keyVersion = currentKeyVersion;
        SecretKey dataKey = getDataEncryptionKey(keyVersion);

        // Generate random IV
        byte[] iv = new byte[GCM_IV_LENGTH];
        secureRandom.nextBytes(iv);

        Cipher cipher = Cipher.getInstance(ALGORITHM);
        GCMParameterSpec parameterSpec = new GCMParameterSpec(GCM_TAG_LENGTH, iv);
        cipher.init(Cipher.ENCRYPT_MODE, dataKey, parameterSpec);

        // Add AAD for additional integrity protection
        if (context != null && !context.isEmpty()) {
            cipher.updateAAD(context.getBytes("UTF-8"));
        }

        byte[] encrypted = cipher.doFinal(plaintext.getBytes("UTF-8"));

        // Format: [version (4 bytes)][iv (12 bytes)][ciphertext+tag]
        byte[] versionBytes = intToBytes(keyVersion);
        byte[] combined = new byte[KEY_VERSION_BYTE_LENGTH + iv.length + encrypted.length];
        System.arraycopy(versionBytes, 0, combined, 0, KEY_VERSION_BYTE_LENGTH);
        System.arraycopy(iv, 0, combined, KEY_VERSION_BYTE_LENGTH, iv.length);
        System.arraycopy(encrypted, 0, combined, KEY_VERSION_BYTE_LENGTH + iv.length, encrypted.length);

        long duration = System.currentTimeMillis() - startTime;
        logger.fine(String.format("Encryption completed in %dms, key version: %d", duration, keyVersion));

        return Base64.getEncoder().encodeToString(combined);
    }

    public String decrypt(String ciphertext, String context) throws Exception {
        if (ciphertext == null || ciphertext.isEmpty()) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Ciphertext cannot be null or empty");
        }

        long startTime = System.currentTimeMillis();
        byte[] combined = Base64.getDecoder().decode(ciphertext);

        if (combined.length < KEY_VERSION_BYTE_LENGTH + GCM_IV_LENGTH + 16) {
            logger.warning("Decryption failed: invalid ciphertext length");
            throw new SecurityException("Invalid ciphertext format");
        }

        // Extract key version
        byte[] versionBytes = new byte[KEY_VERSION_BYTE_LENGTH];
        System.arraycopy(combined, 0, versionBytes, 0, KEY_VERSION_BYTE_LENGTH);
        int keyVersion = bytesToInt(versionBytes);

        // Extract IV
        byte[] iv = new byte[GCM_IV_LENGTH];
        System.arraycopy(combined, KEY_VERSION_BYTE_LENGTH, iv, 0, GCM_IV_LENGTH);

        // Extract ciphertext
        int ciphertextLength = combined.length - KEY_VERSION_BYTE_LENGTH - GCM_IV_LENGTH;
        byte[] encrypted = new byte[ciphertextLength];
        System.arraycopy(combined, KEY_VERSION_BYTE_LENGTH + GCM_IV_LENGTH, encrypted, 0, ciphertextLength);

        SecretKey dataKey = getDataEncryptionKey(keyVersion);

        Cipher cipher = Cipher.getInstance(ALGORITHM);
        GCMParameterSpec parameterSpec = new GCMParameterSpec(GCM_TAG_LENGTH, iv);
        cipher.init(Cipher.DECRYPT_MODE, dataKey, parameterSpec);

        // Verify AAD
        if (context != null && !context.isEmpty()) {
            cipher.updateAAD(context.getBytes("UTF-8"));
        }

        try {
            byte[] decrypted = cipher.doFinal(encrypted);
            long duration = System.currentTimeMillis() - startTime;
            logger.fine(String.format("Decryption completed in %dms, key version: %d", duration, keyVersion));
            return new String(decrypted, "UTF-8");
        } catch (Exception e) {
            logger.warning("Decryption failed - possible tampering detected");
            throw new SecurityException("Decryption failed - data integrity violation");
        }
    }

    public void rotateKey() {
        int newVersion = currentKeyVersion + 1;
        try {
            getDataEncryptionKey(newVersion);
            currentKeyVersion = newVersion;
            logger.info("Key rotation completed, new version: " + newVersion);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            logger.severe("Key rotation failed: " + e.getMessage());
            throw new SecurityException("Key rotation failed", e);
        }
    }

    private byte[] intToBytes(int value) {
        return new byte[] {
            (byte) (value >> 24),
            (byte) (value >> 16),
            (byte) (value >> 8),
            (byte) value
        };
    }

    private int bytesToInt(byte[] bytes) {
        return ((bytes[0] & 0xFF) << 24) |
               ((bytes[1] & 0xFF) << 16) |
               ((bytes[2] & 0xFF) << 8) |
               (bytes[3] & 0xFF);
    }

    private String maskKeyId(String keyId) {
        if (keyId.length() > 8) {
            return keyId.substring(0, 4) + "****" + keyId.substring(keyId.length() - 4);
        }
        return "****";
    }
}
```

