```

**Security Pattern:**
- **HTML Purifier with strict allowlist** - Only safe tags/attributes allowed
- **Separate sanitization levels** - Plain text for usernames, sanitized HTML for comments
- **Twig auto-escaping** - Template engine escapes by default
- **Custom filter for rich content** - Explicit sanitization with |sanitize_html
- **CSP headers** - Defense-in-depth protection
- **Sanitize before storage** - Clean data on input, not just output
- **Prepared statements** - Prevent SQL injection alongside XSS prevention

**Critical PHP XSS Prevention Rules:**
1. Always use htmlspecialchars() with ENT_QUOTES and UTF-8
2. Use HTML Purifier for rich content with strict allowlists
3. Never trust user input - validate and sanitize everything
4. Use templating engines with auto-escaping (Twig, Blade)
5. Set Content-Security-Policy headers
6. Escape output at the point of use, not just on input
7. Use prepared statements to prevent SQL injection
8. Sanitize before storage AND before output (defense-in-depth)

Using `$_REQUEST` for authorization checks is dangerous because it combines `$_GET`, `$_POST`, and `$_COOKIE` values, making your application vulnerable to HTTP Parameter Pollution (HPP) attacks. Attackers can manipulate which value takes precedence by sending the same parameter through different channels.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```php
<?php
// Vulnerable authorization check using $_REQUEST
class DocumentController {
    private $pdo;

    public function __construct($pdo) {
        $this->pdo = $pdo;
    }

    public function viewDocument() {
        // VULNERABLE: Using $_REQUEST allows parameter pollution
        $user_id = $_REQUEST['user_id'];
        $doc_id = $_REQUEST['doc_id'];
        $role = $_REQUEST['role'];

        // Attacker can pollute 'role' parameter
        if ($role === 'admin' || $this->isDocumentOwner($user_id, $doc_id)) {
            return $this->fetchDocument($doc_id);
        }

        http_response_code(403);
        return ['error' => 'Access denied'];
    }

    private function isDocumentOwner($user_id, $doc_id) {
        $stmt = $this->pdo->prepare("SELECT owner_id FROM documents WHERE id = ?");
        $stmt->execute([$doc_id]);
        $doc = $stmt->fetch();
        return $doc && $doc['owner_id'] == $user_id;
    }

    private function fetchDocument($doc_id) {
        $stmt = $this->pdo->prepare("SELECT * FROM documents WHERE id = ?");
        $stmt->execute([$doc_id]);
        return $stmt->fetch(PDO::FETCH_ASSOC);
    }
}
```

**Attack Payload**:
```text
GET /document.php?doc_id=1337&role=user HTTP/1.1
Host: example.com
Cookie: role=admin

// Or via POST pollution:
POST /document.php?role=admin HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

doc_id=1337&user_id=123&role=user
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- `$_REQUEST` merges GET, POST, and COOKIE with configurable precedence (default: GPCS)
- Attackers can inject 'role=admin' via cookies while sending 'role=user' in GET
- Server-side frameworks may parse duplicate parameters differently than expected
- Authorization decisions based on user-controllable 'role' parameter bypass session-based auth

**SECURE VERSION**:

```php
<?php
class SecureDocumentController {
    private $pdo;
    private $session;

    public function __construct($pdo, SessionHandler $session) {
        $this->pdo = $pdo;
        $this->session = $session;
    }

    public function viewDocument(): array {
        // SECURE: Get user info from authenticated session only
        $user = $this->session->getAuthenticatedUser();
        if (!$user) {
            http_response_code(401);
            return ['error' => 'Authentication required'];
        }

        // SECURE: Use specific superglobal, validate input
        $doc_id = filter_input(INPUT_GET, 'doc_id', FILTER_VALIDATE_INT);
        if ($doc_id === false || $doc_id === null) {
            http_response_code(400);
            return ['error' => 'Invalid document ID'];
        }

        // SECURE: Check authorization from server-side session data
        if (!$this->canAccessDocument($user['id'], $user['role'], $doc_id)) {
            $this->logUnauthorizedAccess($user['id'], $doc_id);
            http_response_code(403);
            return ['error' => 'Access denied'];
        }

        return $this->fetchDocument($doc_id);
    }

    private function canAccessDocument(int $user_id, string $role, int $doc_id): bool {
        // Check role from session, not from request
        if ($role === 'admin') {
            return true;
        }

        // Verify ownership in database
        $stmt = $this->pdo->prepare(
            "SELECT 1 FROM documents WHERE id = ? AND (owner_id = ? OR is_public = 1)"
        );
        $stmt->execute([$doc_id, $user_id]);
        return $stmt->fetch() !== false;
    }

    private function logUnauthorizedAccess(int $user_id, int $doc_id): void {
        error_log(sprintf(
            "[SECURITY] Unauthorized access attempt: user=%d, doc=%d, ip=%s",
            $user_id,
            $doc_id,
            $_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR'] ?? 'unknown'
        ));
    }

    private function fetchDocument(int $doc_id): array {
        $stmt = $this->pdo->prepare("SELECT id, title, content FROM documents WHERE id = ?");
        $stmt->execute([$doc_id]);
        return $stmt->fetch(PDO::FETCH_ASSOC) ?: ['error' => 'Document not found'];
    }
}
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **Session-based authorization**: User roles are retrieved from server-side session, never from request parameters
- **Explicit input source**: Use `filter_input(INPUT_GET, ...)` instead of `$_REQUEST` to specify exact parameter source
- **Input validation**: Validate and sanitize all user input with appropriate filters
- **Audit logging**: Log all unauthorized access attempts for security monitoring

For applications requiring flexible parameter sources with complex authorization, you need a robust input validation layer combined with a proper Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) or Attribute-Based Access Control (ABAC) system. Here's a production-ready pattern that prevents parameter pollution while supporting sophisticated permission models.

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```php
<?php
declare(strict_types=1);

/**
 * Secure Input Handler - Prevents Parameter Pollution
 */
class SecureInputHandler {
    private array $allowedSources = [];
    private array $processedParams = [];

    public function __construct(array $config) {
        $this->allowedSources = $config;
    }

    public function get(string $param, string $source = 'GET'): mixed {
        // Validate source is allowed for this parameter
        if (!$this->isSourceAllowed($param, $source)) {
            throw new SecurityException(
                "Parameter '$param' not allowed from source '$source'"
            );
        }

        // Detect parameter pollution attempts
        if ($this->detectPollution($param)) {
            $this->logPollutionAttempt($param);
            throw new SecurityException('Parameter pollution detected');
        }

        $value = match($source) {
            'GET' => filter_input(INPUT_GET, $param),
            'POST' => filter_input(INPUT_POST, $param),
            'COOKIE' => filter_input(INPUT_COOKIE, $param),
            default => throw new InvalidArgumentException("Invalid source: $source")
        };

        $this->processedParams[$param] = $source;
        return $value;
    }

    private function isSourceAllowed(string $param, string $source): bool {
        return isset($this->allowedSources[$param]) 
            && in_array($source, $this->allowedSources[$param], true);
    }

    private function detectPollution(string $param): bool {
        $sources = [
            'GET' => $_GET[$param] ?? null,
            'POST' => $_POST[$param] ?? null,
            'COOKIE' => $_COOKIE[$param] ?? null
        ];

        $presentIn = array_filter($sources, fn($v) => $v !== null);

        // If same param exists in multiple sources, it's pollution
        return count($presentIn) > 1;
    }

    private function logPollutionAttempt(string $param): void {
        error_log(sprintf(
            "[SECURITY] HPP attempt detected: param=%s, ip=%s, uri=%s",
            $param,
            $_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR'] ?? 'unknown',
            $_SERVER['REQUEST_URI'] ?? 'unknown'
        ));
    }
}

/**
 * Permission Service - RBAC with Attribute Checks
 */
class PermissionService {
    private PDO $pdo;
    private array $permissionCache = [];

    public function __construct(PDO $pdo) {
        $this->pdo = $pdo;
    }

    public function hasPermission(
        int $userId, 
        string $resource, 
        string $action,
        array $context = []
    ): bool {
        $cacheKey = "{$userId}:{$resource}:{$action}";

        if (isset($this->permissionCache[$cacheKey])) {
            return $this->permissionCache[$cacheKey];
        }

        // Check explicit permissions
        $hasExplicit = $this->checkExplicitPermission($userId, $resource, $action);

        // Check role-based permissions
        $hasRole = $this->checkRolePermission($userId, $resource, $action);

        // Check resource-specific ownership/attributes
        $hasAttribute = $this->checkAttributePermission($userId, $resource, $action, $context);

        $result = $hasExplicit || $hasRole || $hasAttribute;
        $this->permissionCache[$cacheKey] = $result;

        return $result;
    }

    private function checkExplicitPermission(int $userId, string $resource, string $action): bool {
        $stmt = $this->pdo->prepare("
            SELECT 1 FROM user_permissions 
            WHERE user_id = ? AND resource = ? AND action = ? AND granted = 1
        ");
        $stmt->execute([$userId, $resource, $action]);
        return $stmt->fetch() !== false;
    }

    private function checkRolePermission(int $userId, string $resource, string $action): bool {
        $stmt = $this->pdo->prepare("
            SELECT 1 FROM role_permissions rp
            JOIN user_roles ur ON rp.role_id = ur.role_id
            WHERE ur.user_id = ? AND rp.resource = ? AND rp.action = ?
        ");
        $stmt->execute([$userId, $resource, $action]);
        return $stmt->fetch() !== false;
    }

    private function checkAttributePermission(
        int $userId, 
        string $resource, 
        string $action,
        array $context
    ): bool {
        // Resource-specific ownership checks
        if (isset($context['resource_id'])) {
            $table = $this->sanitizeTableName($resource);
            $stmt = $this->pdo->prepare(
                "SELECT owner_id FROM {$table} WHERE id = ?"
            );
            $stmt->execute([$context['resource_id']]);
            $row = $stmt->fetch();

            if ($row && (int)$row['owner_id'] === $userId) {
                return in_array($action, ['read', 'update', 'delete'], true);
            }
        }

        return false;
    }

    private function sanitizeTableName(string $resource): string {
        // Whitelist allowed table names
        $allowed = ['documents', 'projects', 'reports', 'files'];
        if (!in_array($resource, $allowed, true)) {
            throw new InvalidArgumentException('Invalid resource type');
        }
        return $resource;
    }
}

/**
 * Secure Controller with Full Authorization
 */
class ProductionDocumentController {
    private PDO $pdo;
    private SecureInputHandler $input;
    private PermissionService $permissions;
    private SessionHandler $session;
    private RateLimiter $rateLimiter;

    public function __construct(
        PDO $pdo,
        SecureInputHandler $input,
        PermissionService $permissions,
        SessionHandler $session,
        RateLimiter $rateLimiter
    ) {
        $this->pdo = $pdo;
        $this->input = $input;
        $this->permissions = $permissions;
        $this->session = $session;
        $this->rateLimiter = $rateLimiter;
    }

    public function handleRequest(): array {
        try {
            // Layer 1: Rate limiting
            if (!$this->rateLimiter->check($_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR'], 'document_api')) {
                http_response_code(429);
                return ['error' => 'Too many requests'];
            }

            // Layer 2: Authentication
            $user = $this->session->getAuthenticatedUser();
            if (!$user) {
                http_response_code(401);
                return ['error' => 'Authentication required'];
            }

            // Layer 3: CSRF protection
            if ($_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD'] === 'POST') {
                if (!$this->validateCsrfToken()) {
                    http_response_code(403);
                    return ['error' => 'Invalid request token'];
                }
            }

            // Layer 4: Secure input handling (prevents HPP)
            $docId = (int)$this->input->get('doc_id', 'GET');
            if ($docId <= 0) {
                http_response_code(400);
                return ['error' => 'Invalid document ID'];
            }

            // Layer 5: Authorization check
            $action = $this->getRequestedAction();
            if (!$this->permissions->hasPermission(
                $user['id'],
                'documents',
                $action,
                ['resource_id' => $docId]
            )) {
                $this->logAuthorizationFailure($user['id'], $docId, $action);
                http_response_code(403);
                return ['error' => 'Access denied'];
            }

            // Layer 6: Execute authorized action
            return $this->executeAction($action, $docId, $user);

        } catch (SecurityException $e) {
            error_log("[SECURITY] " . $e->getMessage());
            http_response_code(400);
            return ['error' => 'Invalid request'];
        } catch (Exception $e) {
            error_log("[ERROR] " . $e->getMessage());
            http_response_code(500);
            return ['error' => 'Internal server error'];
        }
    }

    private function validateCsrfToken(): bool {
        $token = filter_input(INPUT_POST, 'csrf_token');
        return $token && hash_equals($this->session->getCsrfToken(), $token);
    }

    private function getRequestedAction(): string {
        return match($_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD']) {
            'GET' => 'read',
            'POST' => 'create',
            'PUT', 'PATCH' => 'update',
            'DELETE' => 'delete',
            default => throw new InvalidArgumentException('Invalid method')
        };
    }

    private function executeAction(string $action, int $docId, array $user): array {
        $this->logAccess($user['id'], $docId, $action);

        return match($action) {
            'read' => $this->readDocument($docId),
            'update' => $this->updateDocument($docId),
            'delete' => $this->deleteDocument($docId),
            default => throw new InvalidArgumentException('Invalid action')
        };
    }

    private function readDocument(int $docId): array {
        $stmt = $this->pdo->prepare(
            "SELECT id, title, content, created_at FROM documents WHERE id = ?"
        );
        $stmt->execute([$docId]);
        return $stmt->fetch(PDO::FETCH_ASSOC) ?: ['error' => 'Not found'];
    }

    private function logAccess(int $userId, int $docId, string $action): void {
        $stmt = $this->pdo->prepare(
            "INSERT INTO access_log (user_id, resource_id, action, ip_address, timestamp) 
             VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, NOW())"
        );
        $stmt->execute([$userId, $docId, $action, $_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR']]);
    }

    private function logAuthorizationFailure(int $userId, int $docId, string $action): void {
        error_log(sprintf(
            "[AUTH_FAILURE] user=%d, doc=%d, action=%s, ip=%s",
            $userId, $docId, $action, $_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR']
        ));
    }
}

class SecurityException extends Exception {}
```

**Defense in Depth Layers**:

1. **Input Source Validation**:
```php
// Configure allowed sources per parameter
$inputConfig = [
    'doc_id' => ['GET'],           // Only allow from GET
    'csrf_token' => ['POST'],      // Only allow from POST
    'session_id' => ['COOKIE']     // Only allow from COOKIE
];
$input = new SecureInputHandler($inputConfig);
```

2. **Parameter Pollution Detection**:
```php
// Automatically detects when same param appears in multiple sources
private function detectPollution(string $param): bool {
    $presentIn = array_filter([
        $_GET[$param] ?? null,
        $_POST[$param] ?? null,
        $_COOKIE[$param] ?? null
    ], fn($v) => $v !== null);
    return count($presentIn) > 1;  // Block if duplicated
}
```

3. **Server-Side Authorization State**:
```php
// Never trust client-provided roles/permissions
$permissions->hasPermission(
    $user['id'],           // From authenticated session
    'documents',           // Hardcoded resource type
    $action,               // Derived from HTTP method
    ['resource_id' => $docId]  // Validated input
);
```

**Additional Protections**:
- **Request signing**: For sensitive APIs, require HMAC-signed requests to prevent tampering
- **Anomaly detection**: Monitor for unusual patterns like repeated authorization failures
- **Principle of least privilege**: Default deny, explicitly grant permissions
- **Permission caching with TTL**: Reduce database load while ensuring timely updates
- **Audit trail**: Log all access decisions for compliance and forensics

No, regex-based filtering is fundamentally insufficient against XSS attacks, especially polyglot payloads that are designed to bypass multiple sanitization methods simultaneously. A polyglot XSS payload works across different parsing contexts (HTML, JavaScript, CSS, SVG) making single-layer regex defenses completely ineffective.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const app = express();

app.use(express.json());
app.use(express.urlencoded({ extended: true }));

// VULNERABLE: Regex-based XSS filtering
function sanitizeComment(input) {
  // Naive attempt to filter script tags
  let sanitized = input.replace(/<script[^>]*>[\s\S]*?<\/script>/gi, '');

  // Try to filter event handlers
  sanitized = sanitized.replace(/on\w+\s*=/gi, '');

  // Attempt to filter javascript: URLs
  sanitized = sanitized.replace(/javascript:/gi, '');

  return sanitized;
}

app.post('/api/comments', (req, res) => {
  const { comment } = req.body;
  const sanitizedComment = sanitizeComment(comment);

  // Store and render - STILL VULNERABLE
  res.send(`<div class="comment">${sanitizedComment}</div>`);
});

app.listen(3000);
```

**Attack Payload** (Polyglot XSS):
```html
jaVasCript:/*-/*`/*\`/*'/*"/**/(/* */oNcLiCk=alert() )//%0D%0A%0d%0a//</stYle/</titLe/</teXtarEa/</scRipt/--!>\x3csVg/<sVg/oNloAd=alert()//>\x3e
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Polyglot payloads work in multiple contexts: as JavaScript URI, HTML event handler, SVG element, and embedded script
- The payload uses case variations (jaVasCript, oNcLiCk) to bypass case-sensitive filters
- URL encoding (%0D%0A) and hex escapes (\x3c) evade pattern matching
- Comments and nested quotes confuse parser-based sanitizers
- Regex cannot properly parse HTML/JavaScript context boundaries

**SECURE VERSION**:

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const createDOMPurify = require('dompurify');
const { JSDOM } = require('jsdom');
const helmet = require('helmet');

const app = express();
const window = new JSDOM('').window;
const DOMPurify = createDOMPurify(window);

app.use(express.json());
app.use(express.urlencoded({ extended: true }));

// Security headers
