**Defense in Depth Layers**:

1. **Double Sanitization**: Pass input through DOMPurify twice to catch mutations that occur during DOM parsing and re-serialization
```javascript
sanitized = DOMPurify.sanitize(normalized, this.domPurifyConfig);
sanitized = DOMPurify.sanitize(sanitized, this.domPurifyConfig);
```

2. **DOMPurify Hooks**: Monitor sanitization in real-time to detect and log mXSS attempts
```javascript
DOMPurify.addHook('uponSanitizeElement', (node, data) => {
