**Defense in Depth Layers**:

1. **Token Security Layer**:
```javascript
// Cryptographically random tokens with SHA-256 hashing for storage
const token = crypto.randomBytes(32).toString('hex'); // 256-bit entropy
const tokenHash = crypto.createHash('sha256').update(token).digest('hex');
// Only hash stored - even with DB breach, tokens can't be reconstructed
```

2. **Account Enumeration Prevention**:
```javascript
// Constant timing responses prevent timing-based enumeration
const MIN_RESPONSE_TIME = 500;
const elapsed = Date.now() - startTime;
if (elapsed < MIN_RESPONSE_TIME) {
  await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, MIN_RESPONSE_TIME - elapsed));
}
// Same message whether account exists or not
