**Never use ECB (Electronic Codebook) mode for encrypting any real data.** ECB mode is fundamentally broken because it encrypts identical plaintext blocks to identical ciphertext blocks, creating recognizable patterns that leak information about your data.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```csharp
